  "definitions": [
    "to pardon, excuse, forgive"
  ],
  "description": "perdonar (first-person singular present perdono, first-person singular preterite perdoné, past participle perdonado)",
  "etymology": "From Vulgar Latin *perdonāre (compare Occitan and Spanish perdonar, Portuguese perdoar, French pardonner, Italian perdonare), from Latin per- + donāre, a loan-translation of a Germanic word represented by Frankish *firgeban (“to forgive, give up completely”), from fir- + geban. Akin to Old High German fargeban, firgeban (“to forgive”), Old English forġiefan (“to forgive”). More at forgive.",
  "page_id": 342471,
  "pronunciations": [
